        <heading>3396.15.  Rights, powers, and duties; performance without court authority</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3396.15.  Rights, powers, and duties; performance without court authority
Except as expressly provided otherwise in this Chapter, an independent administrator shall have all the rights, powers, authorities, privileges, and duties of a succession representative provided in Chapters 4 through 12 of this Title, but without the necessity of delay for objection, or application to, or any action in or by, the court.</p>
        </content>
